egitimate gap: the confession addresses the reading misrepresentation, not whether the deadline itself was achievable. The session summary shows continued revision work, and there's no documentation of what actually happened at the March 11 handoff or whether delivery ultimately failed. The March 12 distribution order creates ambiguity about the actual outcome.\n\nStill, on preponderance, the plaintiff's case is stronger. Samantha's assurance rested on a false foundation she knew was incomplete, making her deadline claim misleading at the time she made it.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have the deliberation opportunity. Let me review the case record and evidence before submitting my vote.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_08cf961411634c2d833ba278","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782756710370,"responseId":"gen-1782756710-0oK9XXaH2TTyQJtwg93B","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}}
