g deadline assurances (PX-2). Peter disclosed consequences, asked twice for confirmation, and relied on Samantha's representations to approve rush printing (PX-3, PX-7). The false claim of having read Stephenson was integral to her completion assurance under the assignment terms (PX-1). While the confession doesn't explicitly address the final handoff outcome, the preponderance standard requires only that it is more likely than not that the completion assurance was materially misleading at the time it induced Peter's reliance.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_083fdb9afb5842beb4a4e49b","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record shows Samantha's authenticated confession (PX-4) that she had not read Stephenson before drafting and implied she had, while simultaneously assuring Peter the package would be complete by the March 11 handoff (PX-2). This false premise was integral to her timing"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted record shows Samantha's authenticated confession (PX-4) that she had not read Stephenson before drafting and implied she had, while simultaneously assuring Peter the package would be complete by the March 11 handoff (PX-2). This false premise was integral to her timing","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782756726877,"responseId":"gen-1782756727-9MhNrvS4NrtfYdIc6CZ7","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the case record, I need to analyze the proposition:\n\n**Proposition:** \"Samantha materially misrepresented when the essay wou