r the package would be complete by the March 11 handoff (PX-2). This false premise was integral to her timing assurance under the assignment terms (PX-1). Peter disclosed consequences, asked twice for confirmation, and relied on her representations to approve rush printing (PX-3, PX-7). Under the preponderance standard, it is more likely than not that Samantha's completion assurance was materially misleading when made and that Peter reasonably relied on it.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782756726877,"responseId":"gen-1782756727-9MhNrvS4NrtfYdIc6CZ7","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}}
